<HEADLINE> 21 People Killed in Bomb Blast in Algeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALGIERS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- At least 21 people were killed and
40 others wounded here today by an explosion of a conventional
bomb, the Algerian news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The explosion took place at a market place in Algiers, the
capital of Algeria, the report said. No one has claimed
responsibility for the blast.
</P>
<P>
Tension is currently prevailing the whole of Algeria after a
series of killings and bombings by terrorist groups. In Madiya
state, some 90 kilometers south of Algiers, a terrorist group
killed 33 people Saturday evening and murdered 44 others four days
earlier, according to well-informed Algerian sources.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a group of terrorists launched an attack Saturday on
a bus in Bubardas state, 50 kilometers east of Algiers, killing
seven passengers and wounding 17 others.
</P>
<P>
Besides, 14 innocent citizens were killed by a terrorist group
Saturday evening in Tibaza state, 70 kilometers west of the
capital city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
