<HEADLINE> Unilever Sponsors Shanghai Scientific Scholarship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A joint Research and Development
Fund was set up by Unilever and the Municipality of Shanghai to
award scholarships to PhD students and experienced scientists.
</P>
<P>
The Research and Development Fund will be used for projects
developing indigenous scientific expertise relevant to Unilever's
consumer goods interests.
</P>
<P>
It will be administered by a council whose membership will be
jointly appointed by the Shanghai Municipality and Unilever.
</P>
<P>
The council will select the projects to be worked upon, will
select recipients of the scholarships and will monitor progress.
</P>
<P>
Applications for the awards will be invited from all
universities and research institutes within the Shanghai
Municipality.
</P>
<P>
Iain Anderson, Unilever's strategy and technology director,
said at the signing ceremony, "Our experiences in Shanghai to date
have clearly demonstrated that there is a rich scientific
tradition within China and their top research institutes employ
some of the world's most eminent scientists."
</P>
<P>
"Through the establishment of this research and development
fund, we look forward to deepening the good relations that have
developed between us and the Chinese scientific community to our
mutual benefit," he added.
</P>
<P>
Present on the occasion of the signing of the agreement today
was a delegation from the co-sponsor, the Shanghai Commission for
Science and Technology, led by Chen Zhili. 
</P>
</TEXT>
