<HEADLINE> Xinhua International News Summary at 1600 GMT, July 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK -- The owners of the Royal Jomtien Resort Hotel will be
among those held responsible for the deaths of at least 90 people
in Friday's tragic fire at the five-star hotel, said Deputy Police
Director General Salang Bunnag on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Investigation showed that guests could not escape the blaze
because the fire exits were either locked or blocked with chairs
to prevent guests from leaving the hotel without paying the bills.
</P>
<P>
The hotel did not have adequate fire safety measures, with
faulty fire escape and fire alarm systems and cooking gas
containers stored inside its kitchen.
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korean Foreign Minister Yoo Chong-ha said today
that the disputed waters between Japan and South Korea should be
zoned before the 1965 fisheries agreement between the two
countries is revised.
</P>
<P>
He also warned that Japan's seizure of South Korean fishing
boats in waters it recently unilaterally declared part of its
200-nautical-mile exclusive economic zone will not help ease
tensions between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Seoul and Tokyo are currently revising the 1965 agreement on
fishing in disputed waters around a barren outcrop of islands in
the Sea of Japan midway between the two countries and which both
countries lay claim to.
</P>
<P>
But South Korea is insisting the existing deal be respected
until a new pact is drawn up. However, Japan unilaterally
redefined its territorial waters by drawing a straight line
through the disputed waters in January without consulting South
Korea.
</P>
<P>
BEIJING -- General Secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) and Chinese President Jiang Zemin
held talks with Do Muoi, general secretary of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV) today at
Beijing's Great Hall of the People on bilateral relations and
issues of common concern and achieved common understanding on a
wide range of issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
