<HEADLINE> Clinton Names Race Initiative Executive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton on
today named Judith A. Winston executive director of his yearlong
effort on race relations.
</P>
<P>
The appointment of Winston, the Department of Education's top
lawyer, was announced as the presidential advisory board on race
relations conducted its first meeting.
</P>
<P>
Winston will work with Clinton, the board and the White House
staff to coordinate the campaign to educate the nation about race,
to promote a dialogue and develop solutions to help bridge the
nation's racial divide, the White House said.
</P>
<P>
She will oversee a staff hired for the effort and to produce a
report on race. 
</P>
</TEXT>
