<HEADLINE> Pakistan, India to Exchange Fishermen Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani and Indian fishermen,
who were arrested for catching fish from the disputed limits of
the Arabian sea, would be released on Tuesday, official sources
said.
</P>
<P>
The step, which is being described as of vital importance for
improvement in bilateral relations, would also help restore
confidence between the peoples of the two countries, the sources
said.
</P>
<P>
A three-member delegation of Pakistan Cooperative Fishermen
Association has left for Bombay to bring back their 194 fishermen
which have been languishing in Indian jails since 1993, they said.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, a team of Indian officials is also reaching Karachi
to take their fishermen back home, they said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
