<HEADLINE> Nepali Minister Rules Out Possibility of Newsprint </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Nepali Finance Minister Rabindra
Nath Sharma promised today that the price of newsprint in Nepal
will not go up in the next fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Sharma told the Lower House he was ready to accept any kind of
punishment should the price of newsprint increase by a single
penny.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali government has come under strong criticism from
parliament members and the print industry after it proposed a
5-percent duty on imported newsprint in fiscal year 1997-98
beginning July 15.
</P>
<P>
The government proposed the duty in the wake of increasing stock
in some countries including neighboring India as a result of
newsprint price fall on the international market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
