<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Poultry Industry Makes Stride </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's poultry industry, which
enjoyed stable business last year, expects to have a record
production value of more than 90 million U.S. Dollars this year,
an official said today.
</P>
<P>
John Smith, chairmen of the Commercial Poultry Producers
Association, said, the 1996 output value in the poultry industry
was estimated to have increased to 50 million U.S. Dollars
compared to 42 million Dollars in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Smith said he is keen for more exports if the industry is to
expand more rapidly, adding that the situation to date is not too
depressing as exports of day-old chicks, hatching eggs, broilers
and table eggs in the past year earned the industry an estimated
five million Dollars.
</P>
<P>
The industry would continue its export to the southern African
region except Zambia, where Zimbabwean poultry is still banned
after the outbreak of Newcastle disease three years ago. 
</P>
