<HEADLINE> Saudi New Shura Council Takes Oath in Inauguration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Members of the new Shura
(Consultative Council) in Saudi Arabia took oath to start their
functions today, reports reaching here from Saudi red-sea coast
city of Jeddah said.
</P>
<P>
The oath was taken before the Saudi King Fahd Bin Abdulah
Aziz at the inauguration session of the council after its formation
according to a royal decree by the King earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
King Fahd wished at the inauguration of the new council every
success for the members in their work for the welfare and
development of the Kingdom and its people, according to Kuwait
News Agency reports.
</P>
<P>
 The council was formed after King Fahd issued a decree on
July 5 to increase the number of the former consultative body from
60 to 91.
</P>
<P>
The mandate of half of the former council members was renewed
for another four years term while the remaining 30 were replaced
by new faces. The new body include a number of technocrats,
academics, social scientists and businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Shura council in Saudi Arabia is a consultative body charged
with the right of providing suggestions and advises to the ruler
to help run the state affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Shura council was first established in the Kingdom in 1993
with only consultative powers. But it had offered advice and
undertaken serious research concerning many issues relevant to
every day life in Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Observers noted that its expansion comes as a further step to
its participation in the decision-making process in the Islamic
Kingdom and certainly an effort to make the council more
productive.
</P>
<P>
King Fahd had issued several royal decrees on the state
systems which included the council of ministers, the Shura
council and the formation of regional assemblies as part of
the Kingdom's drive to run the state affairs more effectively.
</P>
<P>
The council members could discuss the bills and laws issued
by King Fahd although they have no legislative authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
