improvement in the operation of the Niger Basin Authority so that
the resources of River Niger can be properly harnessed.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria's minister of state for foreign affairs, Alhaji
Alhassan Kpaki, suggested that the Council of Minister of the
authority meet at least once a year to approve the budget of the
institution, the News Agency of Nigeria reported.
</P>
<P>
The nine-member authority, composed of Benin, Cameroun,
Burkina Faso, Mali, Cote d'Ivoire, Guinea Bissau, Guinea, Niger
and Nigeria, was formed for cooperation in developing resources
along River Niger.
</P>
<P>
However, the office that administers the authority has been
vacant since 1994.
</P>
<P>
"The authority has not been operating on any approved budget
in the last three years because of the inability of the council
to meet," noted Kpaki after receiving a special message from
Nigerien President Ibrahim Mainasara Baare in Abuja, capital of
Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on behalf of Nigeria head of state General Sani
Abacha, the minister assured that Abacha, in his capacity as
chairman of the Economic Community of West African States, would
expedite action on the appointment of an executive secretary for
the authority.
</P>
<P>
Niger, the current chairman of the authority, has proposed
October 20 as the date for the Council of Ministers meeting to
precede a summit of the heads of state and government of member
countries. 
