<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A Jordanian delegation headed by
Minister of Foreign Affairs Fayez Tarawneh left here this
afternoon to attend a joint Jordanian-Qatari Committee meeting
that will open in the Qatari capital of Doha Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The minister told the press before his departure that the
joint committee will review the development of bilateral ties
since the last meeting in 1996 and discuss the Middle East peace
process and challenges facing the Arab nations.
</P>
