joint agreements.
</P>
<P>
According to official figures, Jordan`s exports to Qatar
reached 17.9 million Jordanian dinars (about 25 million
U.S. dollars) in 1996 compared with 9.9 million dinars (about 14
million dollars) in 1995.
</P>
<P>
While Qatar`s exports to Jordan decreased from 6.4 million
dinars (about 9 million dollars) in 1995 to 6.2 million dinars
(about 8.8 million dollars) in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Qatar was among the Arab nations that cut off ties with Jordan
during the Gulf War crisis due to the kingdom' support for Iraq. But
bilateral ties have been improved in recent years as Jordan
distanced itself from Iraq. 
</P>
