<HEADLINE> Shares Close Higher on European Markets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 14 (Xinhua) - Shares on Europe's major stock
markets ended higher on Monday, with London setting a record.
</P>
<P>
Britain's leading share index hit a record closing high as
investors overlooked the strength in sterling to focus on fresh
takeover speculation, a surge in pharmaceutical stocks and a
bumper sale by chemicals giant ICI. The FTSE-100 ended at 4,857.4,
up 57.9 points.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, shares continued to pursue a relentlessly upward
course as long as the dollar underscores their rally but dealers
were uncertain how long the U.S. currency's support can last. The
DAX-30 index closed at 4,124.19, up 83.22 points. In later
screen-based trade the IBIS DAX index ended at 4,142.19, up 67.89
points.
</P>
<P>
The French stock market was closed for holiday. It will reopen
on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
