<HEADLINE> U.S. Condemns Terrorism in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The U.S. today condemned the
killing of a young Spanish politician by Basque ETA separatists
late last week.
</P>
<P>
Miguel Angel Blanco, a 29-year-old Basque town councillor, was
abducted and shot to death by the ETA separatists. He was found
bound and bloodied with two bullets lodged in his brain on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
U.S. State Department spokesman Nicholas Burns said Washington
"stand side by side with the people of Spain and the Spanish
government in condemning in the clearest and most forceful terms
the vicious terrorism of ETA."
</P>
<P>
The killing also aroused strong condemnation across Europe.
Thousands of Spaniards have gone to to streets to protest the
murder on Sunday. 
</P>
