<HEADLINE> Chinese Symposium On Two Books On Foreign Agression </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The China's Society for People's
Friendship Studies (CSPFS) held a symposium in Beijing today to
announce the release of "From Opium War to Liberation" and
"Reminiscences of Koji Ariyoshi".
</P>
<P>
Israel Epstein, writer of the former, said at the gathering
that his book will help Chinese and foreign readers understand the
history of the foreign invasion of China more accurately.
</P>
<P>
The latter records what Koji Ariyoshi experienced during his
stay in China from 1944 to 1946. Roger Ariyoshi, the writer's son,
said that Koji Ariyoshi's experiences in China made him see that
every nation is free to choose its own path, and should not be
forced.
</P>
<P>
President of the CSPFS Huang Hua said that the publication of
the two books commemorates those foreign friends who supported the
just cause of the Chinese people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
