<HEADLINE> Chinese Official Says Military Enterprises Should Improve </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Vice-premier Wu Bangguo, speaking
at a meeting on military industrial work in Beijing today, said
that military enterprises should improve management and efficiency.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese army has a tradition of self-reliance and hard
work, he said, and it has been carrying a heavy responsibility.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, the output value of some 100 key Chinese
military enterprises has grown by 8.2 percent, and income by 10.9
percent.
</P>
<P>
Because the market environment has greatly changed, the
enterprises must change their managerial methods and operations
along with it, Wu said.
</P>
<P>
"The central government and local governments at different
levels will support the reforms and development of military
enterprises in the same the way they treat civilian enterprises,"
Wu said. 
