<HEADLINE> Genetically Altered Rice Developed In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese scientists have succeeded
in developing a new strain of rice by extracting an anti-herbicide
gene and injecting it into hybrid rice, which got state approval
today.
</P>
<P>
The herbicide used by farmers can kill weeds and low-quality
rice but leave the new strain of rice, thereby improving rice
output, according to experts.
</P>
<P>
The technique will also help reduce the amount of time needed
to check the degree of purity of hybrid rice from four months to
four days, the experts say.  
</P>
</TEXT>
