<HEADLINE> Iraq Plans to Develop Gas Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Iraq has mapped out a plan to
develop its gas industry to meet the needs of southern Europe,
Iraqi Oil Minister Amir Mohammed Rasheed said today in a statement
to the Iraqi News Agency.
</P>
<P>
However, the minister did not elaborate on the plan.
</P>
<P>
The minister said that Iraq, with 3.1 trillion cubic meters of
gas reserves and 112 billion barrels of oil reserves, could
become the world's main gas exporter.
</P>
<P>
Rasheed said that his country is also making efforts to
increase its oil production capacity from 3.5 million barrels per
day (bpd) to 6 million bpd.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the minister stressed the role of Iraqi private
sector in oil distribution and marketing. 
</P>
