<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Ban Styrofoam Food Containers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guangzhou, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The People's Government of
Guangzhou City issued an order today to ban the use of styrofoam
food containers at restaurants and snack bars.
</P>
<P>
The capital of prosperous Guangdong Province will ban them as
of September 1, as one of its moves to free the city of "white
pollution" and make it a safer and healthier place to live.
</P>
<P>
The production, sale, or use of food containers made from
polyethylene or polypropylene will be prohibited because these
items cannot be recycled and they can cause pollution.
</P>
<P>
Substitutes include environmentally-friendly materials like
paper or plant fabrics, according to the order. Recyclable plastic
is also suitable.
</P>
<P>
The government is working out the details of the decree to deal
with imported food that the province packed in non-recyclable
plastic, according to environmental protection officials.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
