<HEADLINE> China's New Round of Ethical and Cultural Development (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China's official body for guiding
ethical and cultural development today urged the whole country to
pay greater attention to more civil language and deeds, a clean
environment, service, and orderly traffic.
</P>
<P>
"Encouraging courtesy and new habits is an important part of
the theme of the Sixth Plenum of the 14th Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China," according to Ding Guangen, a member of
the Political Bureau and the Secretariat, of the CPC Central
Committee.
</P>
<P>
Ding is also director of the Central Commission for Guiding
Socialist Ethics and Cultural Progress. Speaking on a telephone
conference, Ding said, "The CPC Central Committee places great
importance on these activities, which may create a better
environment for the coming 15th CPC National Congress."
</P>
<P>
"This work is helpful in shaping courteous habits and
encouraging healthy trends, demonstrating the Chinese people's
mental outlook of moving forward, and promoting reforms,
development and stability," Ding said.
</P>
<P>
"In order to improve guidance, organize better, and carry these
out well," he said, "we must thoroughly understand the meaning of
these activities in the harmonious development of material
progress and socialist ethical and cultural progress, of helping
the overall situation, and of developing a good image for the
Chinese people."
</P>
<P>
Ding said that civil words and deeds, a clean environment,
better service, and orderly traffic are closely linked to people's
daily work and lives, so improving these things must necessarily
be welcomed by all people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
