<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- All of Hong Kong's government
and aided primary schools will have multi-media computers to
improve the quality of education, an official release said today.
</P>
<P>
The government's Finance Committee has approved funds for the
project.
</P>
<P>
The objective of the provision is to promote computer awareness
among students and to enable teachers to use computer assisted
learning packages for enhancing teaching and learning in primary
schools.
</P>
<P>
