<HEADLINE> Hang Seng Bank Opens Shanghai Branch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's 64-year old Hang Seng
Bank has been given permission by the People's Bank of China to
set up a branch in Shanghai, China's commercial center.
</P>
<P>
It is the first Hong Kong bank to open a branch on the mainland
after Hong Kong's return two weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has 50 overseas financial organizations. The Hang
Seng-Shanghai Branch will go operational in December.
</P>
<P>
The branch is intended to provide good financial services for
Hong Kong and mainland customers, according to sources from Hang
Seng, which has made a considerable effort to promote the economic
development of Shanghai over the past 12 years.
</P>
<P>
Hang Seng set up its first mainland branch in Guangzhou in
1995. 
</P>
