<HEADLINE> China's New Round of Ethical and Cultural Development (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"We should get some real benefits while being practical so that
people can see the actual progress," Ding said, "This is really
meant to serve the people and work in their interests."
</P>
<P>
"We should uphold patriotism, collectivism, socialism, and the
spirit of building an enterprise through arduous efforts. We
should support the establishment of social ethics, professional
ethics, and family virtues," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We must spread the virtues of being polite, being willing to
help others, caring for the collective, being public-spirited,
taking good care of public property, protecting the environment,
abiding by the law, and safeguarding public order," he added.
</P>
<P>
"We should also support the virtues of being career-minded,
being honest, and contributing to the society in order to create
an atmosphere of seeking the true, the good, and the beautiful
while resisting the false, the evil and the ugly," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that the Chinese people should also create friendly
relations and help each other and treat each other as equals.
</P>
<P>
"A healthy and orderly social setting will improve all citizens
and the country's ethical and cultural level as well," he said.
</P>
<P>
"We should rely on the citizens and mobilize them," Ding said,
and called on officials to set a good example for the people.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized that the activities should be practical and
long-lasting and should do away with formalism.
</P>
<P>
Li Tieying, a member of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee and State Councillor, explained that large and
medium-sized cities are the main focus of these activities, and
added, "We should combine improving official management with
serving the people to provide them with convenience and meet their
reasonable demands." Li is also the deputy director of the Central
Commission for Guiding the Socialist Ethical and Cultural
Progress.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion were also leading officials from eight
cities, including Beijing, Shanghai, Tianjin and Guangzhou, and
the Ministry of Construction, and the Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Youth League. The conference was presided over
by Liu Yunshan, deputy head of the Propaganda Department of the
CPC Central Committee and head of the office of the Central
Commission for Guiding the Socialist Ethical and Cultural
Progress. 
</P>
