<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 50th Anniversary of China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A high-profile meeting in Beijing
today marked the 50th anniversary of the founding of the Inner
Mongolia Autonomous Region, China's first autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
Buhe, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National
People's Congress, China's legislature, said that the event
celebrated the 50th anniversary of China's regional autonomy
system for ethnic minorities.
</P>
<P>
He said that in half a century the region has made remarkable
progress in economic and social programs under the leadership of
the Chinese Communist Party and the central government, and that,
"What has been done in the Inner Mongolia Region shows that the
Party leadership is the fundamental guarantor of the
implementation of the regional autonomy policy of ethnic groups."
</P>
<P>
He added that as a state administrative region, the autonomous
region must implement the country's constitution, laws, decrees,
and policies, and work for the nation's interests.
</P>
<P>
He emphasized the unity of ethnic minority groups and the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhaoguo, head of the United Front Work Department of the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, said at the meeting
that the regional autonomy system has guaranteed both the status
of ethnic groups in their regions and the unity of the country.
</P>
<P>
In the past few years, he said, there has been an increase in
ethnic conflicts and religious disputes in some countries and
regions, but, because of its regional autonomy system, China has
maintained ethnic harmony. He went on to say that the fundamental
thing is to improve people's standard of living and narrow the gap
between ethnic regions and other more developed parts of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
