<HEADLINE> Afghan Warring Factions Lack Willingness for Peace: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The UN Special Envoy Norbert
Holl said today that Afghan warring factions especially the
Islamic Taliban militia still lack the willingness to make peace,
Pakistan Television (PTV) reported.
</P>
<P>
"They (the factions) have not yet reached a stage where both
sides are ready to compromise," Holl told reporters today in Kabul
after talks with Taliban's senior leaders, PTV reported.
</P>
<P>
Holl considered the Taliban as being the more belligerent
faction.
</P>
<P>
"The northern alliance in my view is rather ready to
participate in peace initiatives whereas the Taliban, I think,
still see themselves in a stronger position," Holl said.
</P>
<P>
"Afghanistan is no more a forgotten subject" because due to his
initiatives the war-torn country was now "permanently on the
agenda" of the UN Security Council, Holl said.  
</P>
