<HEADLINE> HK to Host World Economic Development Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to host the 6th
Annual World Economic Development Congress from September 16 to 18
this year, sources from the Congress said today.
</P>
<P>
The congress will be a global forum for senior business and
government leaders in power and energy, water and wastewater
treatment, telecommunications, logistics and distribution, and
transportation, according to the Congress.
</P>
<P>
This is the first major international business conference to be
held in Hong Kong following China's resumption of exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
A special keynote speech will be delivered by Tung Chee Hwa,
Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, on
Hong Kong's future role.  
