</P>
<P>
-- AIDS deaths continue to decline in the United States and the
trend is expected to go on, Federal health officials said. The
number of deaths dropped 19 percent, to 30,700 from 37,900, in the
first nine months of 1996 compared to same period of 1995. For
the first time, deaths of women decreased -- although by 7 percent
compared to the 22 percent decline in deaths among men.
</P>
