-- President Clinton summoned Republicans and Democratic
congressional leaders to the White House for a meeting today in
hopes of bringing the last round of balanced budget negotiations
to a conclusion by as early as the end of the week.
</P>
<P>
The Wall Street Journal:
</P>
<P>
-- TWA-crash investigators conducted inflight testing of the
center fuel tank of a chartered 747 off the coast of New York, the
first in a series. The flights are expected to continue for at
least 10 days, and each is supposed to measure a variable that may
have contributed to the July 17, 1996, explosion and crash that
killed 230 people.
</P>
<P>
USA Today:
</P>
<P>
-- President Clinton endorsed a proposed law Monday that would
bar health insurance companies, employers and managed care plans
from discriminating against people on the basis of their genetic
make-up. His support raises the profile of the issue, which has
stirred broad concern as an increasing number of genetic tests
becomes available. 
