<HEADLINE> Eritrea Calls for UN Action Against Sudan's Plot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Eritrean government has
called on the United Nations Security Council to take appropriate
and prompt action against the Sudanese authorities' plot to
assassinate Presidnet Isaias Afwerki of Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
According to the latest issue of weekly "Eritrea Profile"
available here today, Eritrean Foreign Minister Haile Woldetensae
made the appeal in a letter to current President of the UN
Security Council Peter Osvald.
</P>
<P>
In the letter, he noted that the aborted plot to assassinate
President Isaias is "gross violation of the principles of the UN
charter and rules of international law."
</P>
<P>
The minister said that the primary motive behind the
assassination plot is to bring about political confusion in
Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
He accused the Sudanese regime of being prepared to take to
pursuing its objective of subversion, terror and destabilization,
urging the Security Council to take appropriate action without
further delay.
</P>
<P>
Last month, the Eritrean government exposed that the Sudanese
government plotted to assassinate President Isaias, dispatching a
member of its security forces to Eritrea on November 14, 1996 to
infiltrate into the National Democratic Alliance of the Sudan
based in Eritrea "so as to accomplish the abominable act".
</P>
