<HEADLINE> ASEAN to Adopt More Comprehensive Policy Towards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) will adopt a more comprehensive policy
towards Myanmar upon its joining the regional grouping, Malaysian
Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said today.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah, who is also chairman of the ASEAN Standing Committee,
told Parliament that ASEAN's policy and approach, with priority on
constructive engagement at present, was most suited to Myanmar but
on its joining ASEAN, a more comprehensive policy would be
adopted.
</P>
<P>
When Myanmar eventually becomes a member of ASEAN, the
grouping's policy towards the country will change from that of
constructive engagement to a more comprehensive one as certainly
there are other matters and other ASEAN approaches and procedures
which that country is required to observe, he said in reply to
opposition leader Lim Kit Siang during question time in the House
of Representatives.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar along with Laos will be admitted into the regional
grouping at the forthcoming ASEAN Ministerial Meeting on July
24-25 as decided by ASEAN foreign ministers at their special
meeting here on May 31.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah said ASEAN was prepared to give sufficient time to
Myanmar to make changes because the regional grouping understood
the difficulties faced by that country to initiate them in a short
time.
</P>
<P>
He said ASEAN understood the views of other nations over
Myanmar's membership in ASEAN but the decision made by the
regional grouping must be based on the interests of the region and
ASEAN.  
</P>
</TEXT>
