<HEADLINE> HK To Launch Vaccination Program Against Measles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to kick off a large
vaccination program late this month against a predicted measles
epidemic, local newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
Starting from July 28, a total of 580,000 targeted people will
get the free measles shots at 110 government clinics under the
program, the Hong Kong Standard quoted a spokesman for the
Department of Health as saying.
</P>
<P>
More than 50,000 teenagers queued up for appointment slips on
Monday since youngsters aged between 12 and 19 are among the
vulnerable group to the disease.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year, a small outbreak of measles and rubella
affected some 2,000 people in Hong Kong, according to the South
China Morning Post.
</P>
<P>
The government has planned to inject 15 million HK dollars
(about two million US dollars) into the vaccination program, which
aims to inoculate 1.2 million people ahead of an expected measles
outbreak this winter.  
</P>
</TEXT>
