<HEADLINE> Macao to Build Airport-HK Direct Ferry Terminal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Macao is to start construction of a
terminal near its international airport later this year and open a
direct ferry service to Hong Kong by August 1998.
</P>
<P>
Stanley Ho, the Macao casino magnate who headed the Macao
Tourism and Amusement Company, told the local press that his
company is to start construction of the Macao International
Airport Ferry Terminal within the year.
</P>
<P>
Upon completion and operation in the latter half of next year,
passengers to the Macao airport will be able to leave for Hong
Kong directly by boat in a trip that will cost about an hour.
</P>
<P>
Stanley said the plan has been delayed for some time because
there are "some problems yet to be solved." The cost of the
project will also increase, he said, refusing to elaborate.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to boost the competitiveness of the
Macao International airport as the new Hong Kong airport at Chek
Lap Kok will be inaugurated soon.
</P>
<P>
Passengers from Hong Kong can take the direct ferry service to
the Macao airport and those destined for Hong Kong can also take
the service, which is cheaper than via the Hong Kong new airport.
</P>
</TEXT>
