<HEADLINE> Retired Becker Still Plays in Stuttgart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- German star Boris Becker announced
his retirement two weeks ago in Wimbledon but the former world
No. one's own career still carry on.
</P>
<P>
"I'm still playing tennis," said the three-time Wimbledon
champion on Tuesday in Stuttgart at the current Mercedes Cup where
he was seeded seventh.
</P>
<P>
Beckand will begin with a second round match Wednesday against
Karim Alami of Morocco.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old will teamed up with Boris Bachert, from
Becker's hometown of Liemen, and Bjorn Phau joined Nicolas Kiefer,
who proved his talent with a Wimbledon quarter-final place
alongside Becker.
</P>
<P>
He is working alongside coaches Klaus Hofsass, formerly with
the women's Federation Cup team, and Klaus Langenbach to
concentrate on youth players development.
</P>
<P>
But Becker, who last year signed a 10-year contract with
Mercedes for a reported 20 million marks (about 11.5 million
U.S.dollars) is also working on his own form.
</P>
<P>
"I'm here to play tennis," he said. "I'm playing here in the
singles and the doubles (with Kiefer). I hope to win a few matches
this year." 
</P>
