<HEADLINE> Kenya to Launch Project for Boosting Small Firms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A project for promoting Kenyan
small enterprises was launched at a major seminar here today with
1.3 million U.S. Dollars of funds from the U.S. administration.
</P>
<P>
The Micro Private Enterprise Development project is aimed to
promote growth of the agricultural sector in the Mount Kenyan
region, with the injection of the right technology and other
non-financial assistance.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to generate new small agri-related companies in
the area and create at least 5,200 jobs by 2000.
</P>
<P>
The initial research has identified micro-irrigation, animal
feeds manufacture and fruit processing as the focus of the
project.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, affordable manual irrigation pumps,
hay-bales and avocado fruit cosmetics will be provided to the
region.
</P>
<P>
The project will also promote processing of cooking oil using
technology as new business opportunities in the area. 
</P>
</TEXT>
