<HEADLINE> 4 Village Guards Killed by PKK in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Four village guards were killed
Monday night in two clashes with the rebels of the outlawed
Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in eastern and southeastern Turkey,
the semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that when the Turkish security forces were
searching the PKK members near Geziyurdu village in Gurpinar town
of Van province bordering Iran Monday night, the PKK militants
opened fire at the security forces members.
</P>
<P>
During the armed clash between the security forces and the
PKK guerrillas, two village guards were shot dead and one PKK
rebel was also killed.
</P>
<P>
In another development, the agency said that the PKK militants
and village guards exchanged fires in Herekol mountain near
Pervari town of Siirt province late Monday night and another two
village guards were killed in the clash.
</P>
<P>
The agency added that the PKK rebels also took away some 800
sheep after the attack.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Daily News reported today that since the
implementation of Emergency Rule in southeastern Turkey 10 years
ago, 18,019 PKK rebels, 4,209 security forces members and 4,245
civilians have been killed in the armed clashes and raids.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a separatist war in eastern and
southeastern Turkey since August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
