<HEADLINE> Pakistan, India Release Detained Fishermen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Some 193 Indian fishermen who
had been jailed in Pakistan over the last few years were released
today as 194 Pakistani fishermen were simultaneously released from
India's captivity.
</P>
<P>
The swapping of Indian and Pakistani imprisoned fishermen was
agreed upon during a meeting between Indian and Pakistani foreign
secretaries held in Islamabad last month.
</P>
<P>
The Indian fishermen were released from Landhi Jail in Karachi
at about 2:30 p.m., the Associated Press of Pakistan (APP)
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The released fisherman then were flown back home under
arrangements by the Maritime Security Agency (MSA) which had
caught them while they were illegally fishing in Pakistani waters,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Pakistani fishermen, who had been under Indian's
captivity for about four years now, were also released from jails
in India, it said.  
</P>
