<HEADLINE> Spokesman: US Should Not Issue Transit Visas to Taiwan Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China expressed the hope here
today that the United States will not allow Taiwan's leaders to
enter the US on a transit visa so that they can carry on
activities of creating "two Chinas" and "one China, one Taiwan" in
an attempt to split the motherland, and thereby avoid damaging
Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang said that the
US should adhere to the principles of the three Sino-US
communiques and honor what it has said in addition.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remarks at a weekly press briefing in response to
a question about a report that the US government will issue a
transit visa to Taiwan's Lee Teng-hui.
</P>
<P>
Tang said that the Taiwan issue is the most important and most
sensitive issue in Sino-US relations, and that the proper handling
of the issue is the key to a healthy and stable development of
Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Facts show that Taiwan's leaders' real reason for trying to
transit the US is to sabotage the cause of peaceful reunification
of China by creating "two Chinas" and "one China, one Taiwan," and
to damage Sino-US ties, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We have taken note of the fact that the US government has
repeatedly reaffirmed its 'one China' policy and would abide by
the three Sino-US communiques," Tang said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
