<HEADLINE> World Management Conference Opens in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The 1997 World Management
Conference opened here today to discuss Eastern and Western
management cultures.
</P>
<P>
China is the fourth country after Japan, the US, and France to
host the meeting together with the International Federation of
Scholarly Association of Management (IFSAM).
</P>
<P>
More than 400 participants, including international management
scholars from 30 countries and regions and university presidents,
professors, experts and entrepreneurs in China, are attending the
three-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
Participants will present a wide range of views during
discussions of the various topics, including traditional and
modern Eastern management culture, comparison of Eastern and
Western management cultures, the administration trends of the 2lst
century.
</P>
<P>
It is also the first time an international conference has
focused on Eastern management culture.
</P>
<P>
The conference has opened a world management forum, which has
received 329 theses from overseas and Chinese scholars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
