<HEADLINE> Vessel Mishap Kills 75 in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- At least 75 people have been found
dead after a motor vessel carrying nearly 200 passengers sank in a
lake in Indonesia's North Sumatra, the official Antara News Agency
reported today.
</P>
<P>
The accident took place in Toba Lake on Sunday night after the
vessel developed a leak, a local police spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
Most of the passengers were residents who had just returned
from watching the closing ceremony of the Toba Lake festival, the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Lt. Col. H. Amrin Karim, chief of the North Sumatra district
police's information service, said the boat sank because it was
overloaded.
</P>
<P>
He said the vessel which was no longer seaworthy had capacity
of only 50 to 60 passengers.
</P>
<P>
Some passengers who escaped the mishap said they heard the
vessel's bottom wall breaking as the vessel was sailing in the
middle of the lake.
</P>
<P>
The number of casualties was likely to increase as several
passengers were still missing, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
