<HEADLINE> Ingush Calls for Cooperation with Federal Government </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Ingush President Ruslan Aushev
Monday called for closer economic and law enforcement cooperation
with the Russian federal government.
</P>
<P>
Aushev made the call when meeting with Secretary of Russia's
Security Council Ivan Rybkin in Nazran, capital of the Ingush
Republic of Russia.
</P>
<P>
The Itar-Tass news agency reported that at the meeting Aushev
and Rybkin focused on promoting the economic development of Ingush
and preventing violence.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders emphasized the importance to prevent
manifestations of violence, misanthropy, or ethnic strife.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed coordination between law enforcement
agencies, primarily those of the Ingush Republic, the Chechen
Republic, as well as other North Caucasus republics and the
Russian Federation.
</P>
<P>
Rybkin and Aushev also exchanged views on releasing hostages
and effective measures to fight criminal activities, emphasizing
the need to revitalize the commission in charge.
</P>
<P>
Rybkin last night also met with Chechen President Aslan
Maskhadov to discuss the problems concerning restoration of the
Chechen economy. Rybkin left for Moscow after the meeting.
