<HEADLINE> South Korea's Trade Deficit Increases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 15 (Xinhua) -- South Korea's trade deficit in the
first half of this year totaled 9.142 billion U.S. dollars on a
customs-cleared basis, up 1.068 billion dollars from the same
period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the customs administration, exports increased by
0.7 percent to 65.202 billion dollars, while imports were up 2.4
percent to 74.344 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
However, trade balance turned to be a surplus of 97.6 million
dollars in the month of June, the first monthly black figure in
thirty months. The June surplus was a result of slower growth in
imports, stable overseas oil prices and recovering exports of
heavy-chemical goods, said industry and energy officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
