<HEADLINE> Chinese, Lao Vice-Premiers Confer on Expanding Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- During talks between Chinese
Vice-Premier Li Lanqing and Lao Deputy Prime Minister Boungnhang
Vorachith here today, both sides agreed to expand the economic and
trade ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Li said the Chinese government attaches great importance to
Boungnhang's current visit and believes that the trip will fuel
the economic cooperation and trade ties between China and Laos.
</P>
<P>
The economies of China and Laos are complementary and
there is immense potential for the two sides to develop economic
and trade ties, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier noted that the Chinese government regards
economic and trade relations as a cornerstone of China-Laos
good-neighborly ties.
</P>
<P>
He added that China is willing to expand the cooperation with
Laos in trade, investment, and bilateral projects based on the
principles of equality, mutual benefit, effectiveness, long-term
cooperation and common development.
</P>
<P>
Lao Deputy Prime Minister Boungnhang said Laos and China enjoy
the tradition of working with and helping each other. He added
that this conforms to the interests of the two peoples and is
conducive to peace and stability of the region and the world as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
He said Laos is happy to see that the cooperation with China in
politics, economy and trade, education, transport and
communications, and many other fields is expanding and deepening
steadily.
</P>
<P>
Boungnhang said Laos is willing to further increase its
cooperation with China in economy, trade, energy, culture and
education, public health, tourism and other sectors.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, Li and Boungnhang were present at the signing
ceremony of an agreement on economic and technical cooperation
between the two governments.
</P>
<P>
Boungnhang arrived in Kunming in southwest China's Yunnan
Province on July 13 to start his current visit at the invitation of
Li Lanqing.  
</P>
</TEXT>
