<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Henan Province Protects Farmers' Initiative </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- To protect farmers' enthusiasm
for growing grain, China's most populous province of Henan is
taking steps to buy all State-contracted grain that the farmers
want to sell.
</P>
<P>
Henan had a record summer grain harvest of 22.55 billion kg
this year. But farmers were concerned that the resulting lack of
purchasing funds, insufficient storage facilities, and delayed
transportation and sales would cause prices to drop.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government reiterated that the contracted summer
grain of three billion kg remains unchanged, and the purchasing
price will be maintained at 10 percent higher than the state fixed
standard price last year.
</P>
<P>
Henan pledges to buy one billion kg of additional grain by the
end of August at market prices and doesn't allow IOU purchases.
</P>
<P>
It needs some 7.3 billion yuan to buy summer grain and
oil-bearing crops, and localities are making efforts to raise
enough fund.
</P>
<P>
The province has also taken steps to lighten farmers' financial
burdens in a move to encourage them to grow more grain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
