<HEADLINE> Beijing Introduces EMS Phone Service </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The "185" telephone service, a
24-hour special hotline for delivery of express mail is now
available in the Chinese capital.
</P>
<P>
Since mid-June, customers here have been able to dial the
number 185 to get access to the express mail service, give an
operator their address and the service item they need.
</P>
<P>
The express mail service was started in Beijing in 1980, and
now there are approximately 300 EMS delivery vehicles and a staff
of 900 to handle international, domestic and intra-city express
mail delivery, cargo transport, flower delivery, and customs
declaration.
</P>
<P>
Beijing's express mail operation now extends to some 2,000
cities and counties across China, and more than 200 countries and
regions in the world; while its inquiry network connects 201
cities in China and 24 countries and regions internationally.
</P>
</TEXT>
