<HEADLINE> Small Airplane Crashes in Southern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 15 (Xinhua) - A small commercial plane crashed
Monday in Zamboanga province in the southern Philippines with no
one killed, the Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted sources from the Zamboanga International
Airport as saying that the plane developed mechanical trouble
after taking off at 10:30 a.m., prompting the pilot to crash into
the sea nearby.
</P>
