<HEADLINE> NPC Chairman Meets Vietnamese Party Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China's top legislator Qiao Shi
stressed during a meeting with visiting Vietnamese party chief Do
Muoi here today that the sincerity and friendly cooperation
between China and Vietnam will benefit the development of both
countries.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, a standing committee member of the Political Bureau of
the Chinese Communist Party Central Committee and chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress
(NPC), said he is convinced that the relationship between the two
parties and the two countries will become closer and more friendly
through efforts from both sides.
</P>
<P>
Do Muoi, general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV), arrived in Beijing Monday for a
five-day official goodwill visit.
</P>
<P>
China and Vietnam have maintained traditional friendship and
they share basic common points, Qiao noted.
</P>
<P>
He hailed the relationship between the NPC and the National
Assembly of Vietnam as an important part of the friendship between
the two parties, the two countries and the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the contacts between the two sides have been
increasing, Qiao said, expressing the hope that they will further
expand cooperation, learn from each other, and work to safeguard
and advance Sino-Vietnamese friendly relations.
</P>
<P>
At this historic turn of the century, Qiao said, the leadership
and people in China will continue to work hard to further promote
the reunification of the country, to implement the independent
foreign policy of peace, and to develop the friendly cooperation
with neighboring countries and all nations of the world.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed Do Muoi on the construction of China's
socialist democracy and legal system.
</P>
<P>
Do Muoi said that in recent years, the relationship between
Vietnam and China as well as between the two parties have been
sound, adding his purpose for coming to China is to push the
bilateral ties to a higher level, and to ensure that the
good-neighborly relations between the two countries will continue
in the next century.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and China should maintain their friendship from
generation to generation, he said.
</P>
<P>
Do Muoi offered his congratulations on China's resumption of
the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and the great
achievements China has made in its reform and opening up drive. He
also briefed Qiao on the current situation in Vietnam. 
</P>
