registered a turnover of 16.31 million units. It was followed by
the Hong Kong Land which had 4.23 million shares traded. Mulpha
was next with 4.21 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Local computer sound card maker Creative 50 led the gainers of
the day as it rose 1.7 dollars to finish at 29.8 Singapore
dollars. Sembawang Corporation gained 20 cents to end at 7.1
Singapore dollars, while RHB Capital closed 16 cents higher at
4.14 dollars.
</P>
<P>
