<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Society of Trace Elements &AMP; Health Set Up in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Society of Trace Elements and
Health under the Chinese Preventive Medical Association has been
established in this east China metropolis.
</P>
<P>
The society is based in the Baosteel Hospital attached to
Shanghai No. 2 Medical University, and headed by Prof. Kong
Xiangrui, China's leading expert on trace elements and founder of
the science of using trace elements in medical treatment in China.
</P>
<P>
With more than 4,000 members, the society is currently
sponsoring courses on trace elements, bio-inorganic chemistry,
medical geography and other subjects. Its programs are carried out
in more than 30 colleges and universities across China, by 78
research groups, and in more than 700 clinics on trace
elements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
