<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Economic and Trade Fair Ended in East China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QINGDAO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A one-week foreign economic and
trade fair ended today in Qingdao, a coastal city in east China's
Shandong Province, giving a boost to the city's cooperation with
overseas business partners.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,400 participants from 54 countries and regions
attended the fair. Fifteen percent of them are new customers from
Africa, South America, and Southeast Asia. The newcomers brought
in one-fifth, or 230 million US dollars, of the total trade volume
at the fair.
</P>
<P>
More than 40 multinational companies, conglomerates, and
big-name companies signed 250 million US dollars-worth of
contracts, accounting for more than one-fifth of the total trade
volume of the fair.
</P>
<P>
The business volume involved in imports, processing trade and
agents' contracts rose markedly to 180 million US dollars, 130
million US dollars, and more than 22 million US dollars,
respectively.
</P>
<P>
More than 100 projects were signed at the fair with investment
surpassing 10 million US dollars each. Investment in the projects
reached nearly 2.6 billion US dollars, accounting for two-third of
the total overseas investment introduced at the event.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
