<HEADLINE> Russia, Chechnya Discuss Chechen Economic Restoration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Russian Security Council Secretary
Ivan Rybkin and Chechen President Aslan Maskhadov discussed the
restoration of the Chechen economy Monday in Nazran, the Russian
republic of Ingushetia.
</P>
<P>
According to reports from Nazran, the two sides focused on the
rebuilding of the Chechen petrochemical industry and the financing
of measures that aim to restore social order in Chechnya.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed educational and academic cooperation
between their scientific institutions and universities.
</P>
<P>
Moscow and Grozny recently signed three important agreements on
banking, customs and oil transportation through Chechnya to help
restore its economy.
</P>
<P>
Rybkin was accompanied by a delegation of specialists from the
economic, human rights, technological and environmental safety
fields. The experts will be working in Chechnya for several weeks
to ensure interaction between the departments concerned of the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
Rybkin was back in Moscow after the meeting. 
