<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Checkpoint Passing Procedures to Be Simplified at Shenzhen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Passing procedures at three
checkpoints of Shenzhen, Guangdong Province, became simpler as of
today, in a move to increase the speed of vehicles and cargo
across these sites between Hong Kong and Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, at the Huanggang, Wenjindu and
Shatoujiao checkpoints, trucks which formerly were
inspected by customs and frontier departments, respectively, will
now only be inspected by customs.
</P>
<P>
The change was included in a decision jointly made by the State
Commission for Restructuring the Economy, State Economic and Trade
Commission, the Ministry of Public Security and General
Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
Customs officials at the three checkpoints now are expected to
take on the tasks of inspecting service people and their documents
covering vehicles for communications and transport, and will turn
over cases involving illegal immigration to frontier departments,
which formerly did the entire job.
</P>
<P>
Frontier departments now are required to keep the customs
officials informed of problems, and the two agencies will conduct
joint investigations if necessary.
</P>
<P>
On May 1, offices set up at the three checkpoints to carry out
quarantine of animals and plants were closed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
