<DOCNO> XIE19970715.0192 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe's Population Likely to Double in 23 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe's estimated population of
12.3 million people is likely to double in 23 years, according to
the Zimbabwe draft population policy carried out by the National
Economic Planing Commission.
</P>
<P>
The report said that HIV/AIDS is likely to slow down the
population growth rate.
</P>
<P>
It said Zimbabwe's population growth rate of 3.1 percent in
the last 16 years is "too high" and unsustainably against an
annual economic growth rate of 2.1 percent during the same
period.
</P>
<P>
"This becomes critical when the rate of growth of the economy
lags behind that of population. The economic development of
Zimbabwe will reguire an accelerated accumulation of capital
savings. Increased investments in the productive sector of the
economy will foster growth in output and employment," the report
said.
</P>
<P>
The population policy is expectged to help the government
realise achievements in economic, social, and demographic areas
through adjustments in population growth but ultimately it seeks
to improve the quality of life.
</P>
<P>
The draft population policy is complete and will soon be the
subject of a national debate before it is officially adopted by
the government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
