<HEADLINE> China's First SOS Village Develops Kids' Skills </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The SOS Children's Village in
Nanchang, capital city of East China's Jiangxi Province, has
become the country's first orphanage with a diversified
extra-curricular program to foster the children's special skills.
</P>
<P>
The village has adopted 96 orphans since it was set up in
1994. Village officials at the time determined that offering
housing without a specially-designed education program was not
enough.
</P>
<P>
Since the spring of 1995, the orphanage has offered courses in
painting, dance, table tennis and other skills.
</P>
<P>
In these classes, the children soon developed their strong
points: Four kids in the table tennis class won the third
prizes in both the single and team contests in a city
competition.
</P>
<P>
One year later they became the first SOS village children
admitted to the province's physical education school.
</P>
<P>
Many parents in the area have brought their children to the
school to attend the courses.
</P>
<P>
The secretariat of the International SOS Children's Village has
highly praised the Nanchang SOS village, holding it up as a model
for other SOS villages in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
