<HEADLINE> Plavsic Insists on Dissolving Serbian Parliament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Biljana Plavsic, president of the
Republic of Srpska, today refused to revoke her decision to
dismiss the Bosnian Serb parliament.
</P>
<P>
After meeting with Momcilo Krajisnik, Serb member of the
three-man presidency of the Republic of Bosnia in Banja Luka, the
president told reporters that she had no intention to change her
mind.
</P>
<P>
But Krajisnik said despite Plavsic's refusal, the door to
solving the constitutional crisis "remains open," according to the
Yugoslav news agency Tanjug.
</P>
<P>
He said if the parliament abandon its demand for the unseating
of the president, a grace period to discuss all current questions
will be available.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that Plavsic said if the Constitutional Court
decides that her decision to dissolve the parliament violates the
constitution, she will resign.
</P>
<P>
The Plavsic and Krajisnik have been locked in a crisis for
about two weeks following Plavsic's accusation that Krajisnik was
involved in a large-scale corruption.  
</P>
