<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fujian to Wipe out Illiteracy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The government of East China's
Fujian Province has vowed to wipe out illiteracy among young and
middle-aged people by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Some 100,000 people within this age bracket will learn to read and
write 1,500 Chinese characters and pass qualification exams while
180,000 people will attend classes for further study or review
what they have learned.
</P>
<P>
Local educational officials said this will lift the literacy
rate among the young and middle-aged to about 98 percent so that
more farmers are able to update farming techniques and have access
to information needed for improving their life quality.
</P>
<P>
From 1990 to 1996, 1.28 million people in Fujian above the age
of 15 learned to read and write and now 67 counties out of a total
74 in the province have eradicated illiteracy in their regions.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
