<HEADLINE> Piracy Occurs in Uganda's Waters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- In renewed piracy that occurred
last week, at Bugiri in Uganda's Sigulu island near Kenya, two
fishermen were killed and about 250 boat engines were robbed.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today said, the heavily armed prirates
use fast boats and sell the engines to border landing sites in
Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The two fishermen have been the latest victims of the pirates
attack, the report said, adding since 1993 over 30 fishermen have
been killed and many boat engines taken away to areas of Uganda's
neighbouring countries.
</P>
<P>
Some fishermen in the island were quoted as saying, "we have
tried to retrieve the engines with the help of interpol but to no
success." 
</P>
</TEXT>
