<HEADLINE> NZ Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand share market
fell sharply today as the short term interest rates jumped. The
low inflation figure for the latest quarter announced today came
within expectation and had little impact on the market.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 index ended 31 points lower at 2,473 with a turnover
of 52 million NZ dollars (35 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Telecom shares tumbled by 14 cents to 765 cents and accounted
for 20 percent of the turnover, pushing the market down.
</P>
<P>
Other leaders also fell. Fletcher Paper lost 4c to 337c.
Brierley Investment dropped 3c to 134c. Carter Holt Harvey dived
9c to 360c. Air New Zealand dipped 1c to 308c. Lion Nathan slipped
6c to 382c.
</P>
<P>
There were 37 rises and 68 falls.  
