<HEADLINE> Beijing to Develop Multi-Function Vehicles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Beijing plans to build a
multi-function vehicles to meet the estimated rising demand for the
automobiles in the next century, according to "China Business
Times."
</P>
<P>
The vehicles, to be built with domestic parts, are designed to
be both energy-efficient and low-cost, and are expected to meet
the needs of the growing number of buyers of private cars in China.
</P>
<P>
The development of the new automobiles will be supervised by
the Beijing Automotive Industrial Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The project will include two phases of construction work: the
first phase is set to cost a billion yuan to form an annual
production capacity of 30,000 vehicles. The second phase of
construction is expected to lift the annual production capacity to
150,000 at a cost of nearly four billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The funding of the project will be raised from local
enterprises, loans, overseas investment and financing from the
local government. 
</P>
