<HEADLINE> Bonds for Three Gorges Project to be Listed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The bonds issued to fund the
massive Three Gorges Project will be listed on the Shanghai Stock
Exchange for trading tomorrow, the China Securities reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Trading of the bonds, valued at one billion yuan (about 120
million US dollars) and issued between February 28 and March 5,
will be done through investors' securities accounts at the central
registration company of the stock exchange.
</P>
<P>
In denominations of 100, 1,000 and 10,000 yuan certificates and
sold at their face value, the bonds carried an annual interest
rate of 11 percent.
</P>
<P>
The bonds, the first ever issued for the Three Gorges Project
on the domestic market, were rated AAA-, the second-highest rating
possible.
</P>
<P>
The giant Three Gorges Project is the world's largest water
conservancy on the Yangtze River, China's longest. Total cost of
the project is estimated at 90 billion yuan at 1993 prices, or
203.4 billion yuan in dynamic prices by the time of its completion
in 2009. 
</P>
</TEXT>
