<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Stiff business competition on the
global market today and the approaching free trade era should
prompt Asia-Pacific countries to set up a business network, a
senior official said.
</P>
<P>
Opening a conference on establishing a cooperative and small
enterprise network in the Asia-Pacific Region here Monday,
Coordinating Minister for Production and Distribution Hartarto
said with such a network, managers of cooperatives and small
enterprises would be able to exchange information, knowledge and
experience.
</P>
<P>
