<HEADLINE> Apple's World Tour Arrives in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Apple Computer Inc. brought Apple
Technology World Tour '97 for Chinese developers, solution
providers, and multimedia content publishers to Beijing on
Monday, "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The tour provided an overview of Apple's strategic directions
and key technologies for developers, with an emphasis on the
latest developments in interactive media, Java, the Internet, the
Mac OS and Rhapsody, Vencent Tai, Apple manager for China business,
was quoted as saying at the event.
</P>
<P>
The demonstration also gave Chinese developers their first look
at an early version of Rhapsody, the code name for Apple's
next-generation operating system using Apple and Next technologies,
Tai said.
</P>
<P>
Prior to China, the tour had been to Munich, London, Stockholm,
Paris, Tokyo and Seoul. It will also travel to Bombay and Sao
Paolo later this month and to Mexico City next month.
</P>
<P>
The one-day format was designed to maximize technical content.
</P>
<P>
The event also showed how technologies such as Quick Time 3.0
will continue to define the standard for cross-platform
multimedia.
</P>
<P>
Apple announced that its Mac OS 8, the next major release of
the Mac operating system which will be released later this year,
will reopen a significant gap between the Mac OS and Windows 95.
</P>
<P>
Despite its poor performance in other parts of the world, Apple
enjoyed a 42 percent rise in its sales in China in the third
quarter of its 1997 fiscal year, Apple statistics
indicated. 
</P>
