<HEADLINE> Tsingtao Beer Expands into Group Enterprise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Tsingtao Brewery Group Co Ltd,
China's leading beer producer and one of the country's few
international brands, was launched recently in the east coastal
city of Qingdao, Shandong Province.
</P>
<P>
The group, a wholly owned State enterprise registered with the
State shares of the previous Tsingtao Brewery Co Ltd holds 44.42
percent of the shares of the Tsingtao Brewery Co Ltd, valued at
399.8 million yuan (49.17 million US dollars), the
English-language newspaper China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
Tsingtao Brewery Group Co Ltd is in a three-tier structure: a
real estate company, an advertising company and other business
companies held by the group -- non-binding enterprises contracted
with the group.
</P>
<P>
Li Guirong, chairman of the group's board of directors, called
this move another significant capital operation after Tsingtao
Beer was restructured into a joint stock company in 1993.
</P>
<P>
The move is an attempt to rebuild Tsingtao's image in the stock
markets -- ensuring good returns for investors, advancing
multiplied businesses and merging small beer producers to promote
large production.
</P>
<P>
Tsingtao was the first inland company listed in the Hong Kong
Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
Tsingtao produced 350,000 tons of beer in 1996, ranking third
in China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
