<HEADLINE> China Construction Bank Enters Inter-Bank Bond Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank has
concluded its bond dealings on the stock exchanges and turned to
the inter-bank bond market as required by the central bank.
</P>
<P>
A bank official said that the bank now trades and repurchases
treasury bonds through an inter-bank bond trading system, and the
Central Bond Registration Co. Ltd. has become the new custodian of
all the state treasury bonds owned by the bank.
</P>
<P>
The People's Bank of China, the central bank, issued a circular
in early June to stop bond dealings on the stock exchanges and
stock trading centers across the country, in a bid to cut the bank
funds off from the stock market.
</P>
<P>
The China Construction Bank was designated as the primary dealer
of state treasury bonds in February, 1995, and has since
underwritten 35.4 billion yuan in treasury bonds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
