<HEADLINE> Drug Use Up in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican police authorities
have noticed an increase in the consumption of narcotics in the
country as indicated by a rise in seizures of the drug known as
"crack."
</P>
<P>
More than 12,000 pieces of crack were seized in the first six
months of the year. Only 17,800 pieces were confiscated throughout
last year, police said.
</P>
<P>
Most of the crack, about 7,100 pieces, was seized in San
Jose. The Atlantic port of Limon and the Pacific port of
Puntarenas are the other two main transshipment centers for the
drug.
</P>
<P>
Crack is cheaper and more harmful than cocaine.
</P>
<P>
Police said the seizures of cocaine and marijuana have also
increased. 
