<HEADLINE> US Engines to Power Air China's Boeing 777s </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Air China, China's flag-carrier,
has selected US-based Pratt &AMP; Whitney's PW 4000 engines to propel
its Boeing 777 aircraft, the "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The selection was made in a contract for engine support that
Air China, a major international airline in China, has signed with
China Aviation Supplies Import and Export Corp. and Pratt &AMP;
Whitney, a leading producer in aircraft propellers.
</P>
<P>
Under the 170-million-dollar contract, Air China will buy 10
installed and three spare engines for its five boeing 777
airplanes. Deliveries will begin in October 1998. 
</P>
