<HEADLINE> Italy to Host Ministerial Meeting on Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini said today that a meeting of foreign ministers from relevant
countries will be held at the end of this month to discuss new
initiatives to help restore stability in Albania after the general
elections on June 29 put a new cabinet to place.
</P>
<P>
Meeting envoys of 14 European Union members to Italy, Dini said
that new international assistance should be ensured in the
economic reconstruction of the Balkan country as the date for the
Italy-led multinational forces to withdraw approaches.
</P>
<P>
Dini said the meeting of foreign ministers on July 31 in Rome
will pave the way for an international conference on Albania in
September or October.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian Socialist Party led by Fatos Nano won a landslide
victory over President Sali Berisha's Democratic Party in the
internationally-monitored June 29 elections. Berisha has pledged
to step down once the Socialist-led coalition government is in
place. 
</P>
