<HEADLINE> Highlights of Major Beijing-Based Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Highlights of today's major
Beijing-based newspapers:
</P>
<P>
"People's Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- General Secretary of the Central Committee of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) and Chinese President Jiang Zemin held talks
with Do Muoi, general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of Vietnam (CPV), in Beijing yesterday on bilateral
relations and issues of common concern, and achieved common
understanding on a wide range of issues.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin expressed his hope that the US
Westinghouse Electric Co. would increase its cooperation and
investment in China, at a meeting with Michael Jordan, chairman
and chief executive officer of Westinghouse yesterday in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese President Jiang Zemin paid a visit to an art
exhibition on the return of Hong Kong to the motherland at the
Museum of the Chinese Revolution in Beijing yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, with some 2,200 paintings on display, was
sponsored by the Chinese Ministry of Culture to highlight the
Chinese people's struggles over the past century against foreign
invasions.
</P>
<P>
-- Qiao Shi, chairman of China's National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee, met yesterday in Beijing with a
delegation from Patriotic Movement of Salvation (PMS) of Chad,
which is on a good-will visit to China at the invitation of the
Communist Party of China (CPC)
</P>
<P>
Qiao, also a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, said that the CPC is pleased
with the smooth development of its friendly and cooperative ties
with PMS since the two established relations in 1991.
</P>
<P>
-- Qiao Shi said in Beijing yesterday that the leaders of China
and Germany should view bilateral ties from a strategic
perspective to secure a healthy and stable relationship between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks while meeting with Herta Daeubler-Gmelin,
vice-chairman of Germany's Social Democratic Party (SDP), and her
party.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- A strict regulation was issued in Beijing yesterday asking
Communist Party members to observe discipline in promotions or
dismissals of cadres.
</P>
<P>
Issued by the General Office of the Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Party, the regulation says that promotions and
dismissals can be done only after being discussed by a Party
committee instead of being decided by a small number of
people.
</P>
<P>
-- China's fisheries experienced a two-digit growth in
production during the first five months this year, stablizing the
sector as a supplier of protein.
</P>
<P>
By the end of May, the output of aquatic products reached 9.12
million tons, up 11.3 percent from the same period last year,
according to the Ministry of Agriculture. 
</P>
