<HEADLINE> Joint NATO Military Exercise Begin in Slovakia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A five-day joint military exercise
by several North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) members and
partners of the Western military alliance began in Slovakia today.
</P>
<P>
Air forces of the United States, Italy, Turkey, France,
Austria, the Czech Republic, Hungary, Romania, Slovakia and other
countries have joined the military exercise.
</P>
<P>
Operation "Coordination Key" is aimed at improving the
coordination in the air with each other in fighting and getting
experience of evacuating civilians during war time, said a
spokesman for the Ministry of National Defense of the Czech
Republic.
</P>
<P>
The exercise has been one of the largest that were launched in
Slovakia in recent years, press reports said. 
</P>
