<HEADLINE> UN Envoy Leaves for Kabul Today on Peace Mission </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations Special Envoy
Norbert Holl leaves here today for Kabul to undertake the UN
mission to bring peace to Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
His shuttle diplomacy is part of hectic efforts to bring about
an intra-Afghan dialogue for the settlement of Afghan crisis under
the UN auspices.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Afghanistan Holl is believed to discuss the
setting up of a political commission with the leaders of Afghan
Islamic Taliban militia.
</P>
<P>
The proposed commission will take care of the cease-fire,
exchange of prisoners and the outlines for a broad-based
government in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Last week, the UN Envoy visited Mazar-e-Sharif, Afghanistan's
northern major city, and held extensive talks with the leaders of
the anti-Taliban northern Alliance and discussed the same issues
in detail.  
</P>
