<HEADLINE> Sotomayor Regains Top Form </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Javier Sotomayor of Cuba regained
his top form to set this year's second best mark of 2.34 meters at
an international athletics meeting in Salamanca, Spain, on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sotomayor produced his best performance since February last
year at the scene of his high jump world record four years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban, who was the 1991 and 1993 world champion, wrote the
world best of 2.45 meters at the corresponding meeting in 1993.
</P>
<P>
Sotomayor has sustained knee and ankle operations since he
limped away from the Olympic final last August when he could only
finish 11th. 
</P>
