<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Coffee Exports Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian coffee exports
increased 147.7 percent in value and 101 percent in volume
during the first half of this year compared with the same
period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Coffee exports reached 7.56 million sacks each weighing 60
kilograms for a total of 1.379 billion dollars between January and
June, said a report by the Brazilian Association of Coffee
Exporters published today by the press.
</P>
<P>
In June Brazilian exports reached 998,800 sacks, 33
percent up over the same month last year.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is the world's biggest coffee grower and exporter.
Last year it produced 23.5 million sacks of coffee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
