<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Australian Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading Australian newspapers today:
</P>
<P>
The Australian
</P>
<P>
-- Australia's leading mining company BHP is looking to buy
into Indonesia's biggest steel maker less than two months after
unveiling plans to sack more than 2,000 employees from its
Australian steelworks.
</P>
<P>
The Sydney Morning Herald
</P>
<P>
-- The New South Wales state government has backed down on its
introduction of a bed tax in a move to get the major Sydney hotels
to hand over their rooms to the Sydney Olympics organizers.
</P>
<P>
The Age
</P>
<P>
-- Australia's Ambassador in Phnom Penh yesterday denied that
his embassy had refused asylum to frightened opponents of
Cambodian co-Prime Minister Hun Sen in the aftermath of the
violent ousting of Hun Sen's coalition partner.
</P>
<P>
The Australian Financial Review
</P>
<P>
-- Gloweave, a top home-grown brand name shirt producer in
Australia, is closing its last remaining Australian factory. The
company, which blames the closure on falling levels of protection,
turns over about 15 million US dollars a year and accounts for 15
percent of the nation's branded business shirt market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
