<HEADLINE> Gery Breaks 24-hour Cycling Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Mickael Gery of France Monday set a
new world outdoor record of 769.005 kilometers for a 24-hour cycle
ride in Cleder, France.
</P>
<P>
Gery, riding at a velodrome in this north-west French town,
bettered the former record of 738.100km of compatriot Laurent
Drouault, set on a road circuit.
</P>
<P>
American Michael Secrest holds the record of 857km for a
24-hour ride in an indoor velodrome. 
</P>
</TEXT>
