<HEADLINE> Dominguez to Defend WBC Title Against Tafer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- World Boxing Council cruiserweight
champion Marcelo Dominguez of Argentina will defend his title
against Frenchman Akim Tafer on August 16 at Cannet-Rocheville in
the south of France, promoters announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
Dominguez was earlier slated to face another Frenchman, Fabrice
Tiozzo, but that bout was cancelled after contractual difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Dominguez has a 21-1-1 record while former European champion
Tafer has a 23-6 log. 
</P>
</TEXT>
