<HEADLINE> Brazil to Import Natural Gas From Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Brazilian government
is negotiating with its Peruvian counterpart the purchase of
Peruvian natural gas, Brazilian authorities said today.
</P>
<P>
Last month Brazilian Mining and Energy Minister Raimundo Tritto
visited Peru to discuss the possibility of pumping gas from the
Peruvian province of Camisea which has a deposit of about 2.5
billion barrels of petroleum. 
</P>
