<HEADLINE> Echoes From The Mercosur (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 14 (Xinhua) --
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The administrative secretary of the Southern
Common Market (Mercosur) issued its first official bulletin
on July 9.
</P>
<P>
The bulletin contains the institutional regulations and
projects approved for the four member countries of the bloc, as
well as resolutions, decisions and directives.
</P>
<P>
The bulletin will be a fundamental tool for all public and
private companies and institutions that have any relation or
interest in the Mercosur.
</P>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO -- The Formula 3, a car race in which Argentine,
Brazilian, Chilean, Paraguay and Uruguayan drivers will compete,
will be held on October 29.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Argentine President Carlos Menem will leave
on August 5 for La Paz, Bolivia to attend the inaugural ceremony
of Bolivian President-Elect Hugo Banzer Suarez, announced the
Argentine Foreign Ministry.
</P>
<P>
On August 7 Menem will receive Chilean President Eduardo Frei
in Mendoza. He will pay a return visit the following day in
Santiago to inaugurate a gas pipeline that will join their two
countries.
</P>
<P>
On August 23 and 24, the president of Argentina will take
part in the 11th summit of heads of state of the Rio group to be
held in Asuncion, Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The Cristo Redentor International Tunnel,
which connects Chile and Argentina, was closed to vehicular
traffic again on July 8 due to the state of the highways
after a snowfall.
</P>
<P>
The international tunnel will remained closed until further
notice, since the asphalt has been covered by a layer of ice and
is very dangerous for driving.
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- The Brazilian government will eliminate
quotas on sugar exports starting next year, announced Mauricio
Assis, commodities secretary of Brazil's Ministry of Industry,
Commerce and Tourism.
</P>
<P>
The current sugar export quota for companies authorized by
the government is 5.3 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is the world's biggest producer and exporter of sugar.
Last year it produced 12 million tons and exported a little over
5 million tons. (to be continued)



nnnn
</P>
