<HEADLINE> Nasdaq Market Soaring to New High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Major technology stocks drove the
Nasdaq market to a record close for the eighth straight session,
but the broad market ended nearly unchanged Monday after giving up
almost all the gains which brought it to new highs.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average rose 1.16 to 7,922.98 points
after erasing a 61-point deficit over the last half hour and
surrendering a 29-point gain earlier.
</P>
<P>
The technology-laid Nasdaq composite index rose 21.26 points to
1,523.88, giving it an eight-session gain of 85 points, or nearly
6 percent.
</P>
<P>
Microsoft, Dell, Compaq and Hewlett-Packard all rose over the
past two sessions as a result of encouraging second-quarter
results.
</P>
<P>
Advancers outnumbered decliners by a small margin on the NYSE,
where volume totaled 485.86 million shares, down from 509.89
million on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500-stock list rose 1.70 to 918.38, and
the NYSE composite index slipped 0.01 to 478.11. Both indexes
retreated from morning gains that would have set new highs.
</P>
<P>
The American Stock Exchange composite index fell 2.84 to
632.63. 
</P>
</TEXT>
