<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IMF Approves Third Annual Loan for Mauritania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary Fund
(IMF) approved today the third annual loan under the Enhanced
Structural Adjustment Facility (ESAF), in an amount to some 20
million U.S. dollars for Mauritania.
</P>
<P>
The loan, which is available in two equal semiannual
installments, is provided to support Mauritania's economic program
in 1997. The three-year ESAF credit, for the equivalent of some 59
million dollars was approved in January, 1995.
</P>
<P>
The western African country's economic program in 1997 is
targeted to achieve a real GDP growth rate of 4.9 percent, hold
the inflation rate at 5 percent and limit the external current
account deficit to about 5.5 percent of GDP.
</P>
<P>
Mauritania joined the IMF in September 1963. Its quota is about
66 million dollars and its outstanding use of IMF financing
currently totals some 100 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The ESAF is a concessional IMF facility for assisting member
countries that are undertaking economic reform programs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
