<HEADLINE> IFC Approves First Investments in Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The International Finance
Corporation (IFC) today announced the approval of its first four
investments totaling 11.1 million U.S. dollars equivalent in the
Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
These investments include a 5 million dollar loan for
Makedonija Turist A.D., one of the country's largest tourism
companies, a 1.5 million dollar loan for Teteks A.D., a textile
company based in Tetovo, a 3.8 million dollar loan for
construction materials company, Nikol-Fert and 0.8 million dollars
investment for Msinomont Company, a small producer of standard and
specialty machinery for the glass working industry.
</P>
<P>
IFC is a member of the World Bank Group and the largest
multilateral source of equity and loan financing for private
sector in developing countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
