<DOCNO> XIE19970715.0291 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UN Observers Condemn UNITA's Actions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Observers and observers on
Angolan peace process from the U.S., Russia and Portugal today
jointly denounced the National Union for the Total Independence
of Angola (UNITA) for detaining a U.N. plane in east Angola.
</P>
<P>
On July 11 to 12, UNITA detained a UN helicopter engaged in
investigation missions in North Lunda province for 24 hours, it
said, adding that earlier than this on June 7, UNITA also
detained a plane of the World Food Program in Moxico province in
southeastern Angola.
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement, the two also blamed UNITA for abusing UN
personnel and non-governmental organization staff working in the
area, saying the actions have violated the Lusaka Peace Accord
and the resolutions by the UN Security Council, as well as the
spirit announced by the political committee of UNITA on June 16,
in which UNITA promised investigation into cases violating peace
wishes to avoid further recurrences.
</P>
<P>
The statement finally requests that UNITA abide by its
promises and, in a responsible manner, prevent any incidences
from bringing harm to the present situation. Meanwhile, it
appeals to the United Nations to include the recent incidents
into its agenda. 
</P>
</TEXT>
